Visits to primary care, a doctor, cost $11.

A visit to a specialist cost $32, same as a visit to the ER. Ambulance transport cost $16-32

tweet:
Child care is reduced cost, based on your income, some pay $100 per month, others $400.

Children have free healthcare until they're 20, and I think dental is free until 25.

Prescription drugs have an annual cap of $250. A nights stay at the hospital cost $12.

I had 1.5 years of maternity leave for each of my children, then my husband took over & had a year of paternity leave.

We received 80-85% of our ordinary salary + the child benefit of around $110 dollar per child & month.
